TITLE: ThreadX Managed Interrupt Handler Template (Assembly)
DESCRIPTION: This assembly code provides a template for a ThreadX managed interrupt handler. It demonstrates the standard structure for ISRs, allowing access to ThreadX services from the interrupt context. It includes pushing and popping registers to preserve the context and branching to a C interrupt routine.
SOURCE: https://github.com/stmicroelectronics/stm32cubeh5/blob/main/Middlewares/ST/threadx/ports/cortex_m4/ac6/readme_threadx.txt#_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: assembly
CODE:
```
        .global  __tx_IntHandler
        .thumb_func
__tx_IntHandler:
; VOID InterruptHandler (VOID)
; {
        PUSH    {r0, lr}

;    /* Do interrupt handler work here */
;    /* BL <your interrupt routine in C> */

        POP     {r0, lr}
        BX      lr
; }
```

