TITLE: Create EC Self-Signed Certificates (Shell)
DESCRIPTION: These commands generate EC self-signed certificates using OpenSSL. It includes generating a private key, creating a certificate signing request, and converting the key and certificate to DER format for use in embedded systems.  This example uses the secp384r1 elliptic curve.
SOURCE: https://github.com/stmicroelectronics/stm32cubeh5/blob/main/Middlewares/ST/netxduo/addons/azure_iot/samples/README.md#_snippet_5

LANGUAGE: Shell
CODE:
```
# Generate private key and certificate (public key). Note: The comman name must be device id.
openssl req -new -x509 -nodes -days 365 -newkey ec:<(openssl ecparam -name secp384r1) -keyout privkey.pem -out cert.pem -config x509_config.cfg -subj "/CN=<Same as device Id>"

# Convert format from key to der.
openssl ec -outform der -in privkey.pem -out privkey.der

# Convert format from cert pem to der.
openssl x509 -outform der -in cert.pem -out cert.der
```

