TITLE: STM32CubeIDE Linker Configuration for ThreadX Heap
DESCRIPTION: This snippet illustrates how to configure the linker file in STM32CubeIDE for ThreadX dynamic memory allocation. It defines a new section named ._threadx_heap within the linker script.  This section provides a dedicated memory area for ThreadX's heap, ensuring that ThreadX can dynamically allocate memory as needed.  The example sets the heap size to 64KB and specifies its location within the RAM_D1 region.
SOURCE: https://github.com/stmicroelectronics/stm32cubeh5/blob/main/Projects/STM32H573I-DK/Applications/USBX/Ux_Host_HID_CDC_ACM/README.md#_snippet_2

LANGUAGE: text
CODE:
```
._threadx_heap :
  {
     . = ALIGN(8);
     __RAM_segment_used_end__ = .;
     . = . + 64K;
     . = ALIGN(8);
   } >RAM_D1 AT> RAM_D1
```

