TITLE: Standard IRQ Handler in Assembly
DESCRIPTION: This is the default IRQ handler defined in tx_initialize_low_level.S. It saves the system context by jumping to _tx_thread_context_save, then restores the context by jumping to _tx_thread_context_restore. Application-specific ISR calls should be placed between these two calls. This snippet is written in ARM assembly.
SOURCE: https://github.com/stmicroelectronics/stm32cubeh5/blob/main/Middlewares/ST/threadx/ports/cortex_a7/gnu/readme_threadx.txt#_snippet_3

LANGUAGE: assembly
CODE:
```
    .global __tx_irq_handler
    .global __tx_irq_processing_return      
__tx_irq_handler:
@
@    /* Jump to context save to save system context.  */
    B       _tx_thread_context_save             @ Jump to the context save
__tx_irq_processing_return:
@
@    /* At this point execution is still in the IRQ mode. The CPSR, point of
@       interrupt, and all C scratch registers are available for use. Note 
@       that IRQ interrupts are still disabled upon return from the context
@       save function.  */
@
@    /* Application ISR call(s) go here!  */
@
@    /* Jump to context restore to restore system context.  */
    B       _tx_thread_context_restore
```

