TITLE: Convert DER to Hex Array (Shell)
DESCRIPTION: These commands convert the DER-formatted certificate and private key files into C header files containing hex arrays. The arrays can then be included in the embedded application for X.509 authentication. This uses `xxd` and `sed` to format the output.
SOURCE: https://github.com/stmicroelectronics/stm32cubeh5/blob/main/Middlewares/ST/netxduo/addons/azure_iot/samples/README.md#_snippet_6

LANGUAGE: Shell
CODE:
```
echo "#include \"nx_api.h\"\n/**
device cert (`openssl x509 -in cert.pem -fingerprint -noout | sed 's/://g' `) :\n`cat cert.pem`\n\ndevice private key :\n`cat privkey.pem`\n*/\n" > sample_device_identity.c

xxd -i cert.der | sed -E "s/(unsigned char) (\w+)/\1 sample_device_cert_ptr/g; s/(unsigned int) (\w+)_len/\1 sample_device_cert_len/g" >> sample_device_identity.c
xxd -i privkey.der | sed -E "s/(unsigned char) (\w+)/\1 sample_device_private_key_ptr/g; s/(unsigned int) (\w+)_len/\1 sample_device_private_key_len/g" >> sample_device_identity.c
```

