TITLE: Creating Header File Symbolic Links
DESCRIPTION: This snippet iterates through the ThreadX, NetX Duo, and FileX libraries to create symbolic links for all header files in a common include directory within the build directory. It ensures that all necessary header files are easily accessible for compilation.
SOURCE: https://github.com/stmicroelectronics/stm32cubeh5/blob/main/Middlewares/ST/usbx/test/cmake/libs/CMakeLists.txt#_snippet_8

LANGUAGE: CMake
CODE:
```
foreach(lib threadx netxduo filex)
  get_target_property(dirs ${lib} INCLUDE_DIRECTORIES)
  execute_process(COMMAND mkdir -p ${CMAKE_BINARY_DIR}/inc)
  foreach(dir ${dirs})
    file(GLOB header_files ${dir}/*.h)
    foreach(header_file ${header_files})
      execute_process(COMMAND ln -sf ${header_file} ${CMAKE_BINARY_DIR}/inc)
    endforeach()
  endforeach()
endforeach()
```

