TITLE: User Option Bytes Configuration (TrustZone)
DESCRIPTION: This snippet shows the required user option bytes configuration for enabling TrustZone security and defining secure/non-secure memory regions. TZEN enables TrustZone, SECWM1_STRT/END define the secure Flash region (Bank1), and SECWM2_STRT/END define the non-secure Flash region (Bank2).
SOURCE: https://github.com/stmicroelectronics/stm32cubeh5/blob/main/Projects/NUCLEO-H563ZI/Examples/GTZC/GTZC_TZSC_MPCBB_TrustZone/README.md#_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: none
CODE:
```
TZEN=B4
SECWM1_STRT=0x0  SECWM1_END=0x7F    meaning all 128 pages of Bank1 set as secure
SECWM2_STRT=0x1  SECWM2_END=0x0     meaning no page of Bank2 set as secure, hence Bank2 non-secure
```

