TITLE: Customizing USART Commands List in OpenBootloader (C)
DESCRIPTION: This code snippet demonstrates how to customize the list of supported commands for the USART interface in the OpenBootloader application. It defines a custom command structure `OPENBL_CommandsTypeDef` and assigns function pointers to the `OPENBL_USART_ReadMemory` and `OPENBL_USART_WriteMemory` functions, effectively limiting the supported commands to read and write operations. The USART handle is then initialized with this custom command list, and the list is registered within the middleware.
SOURCE: https://github.com/stmicroelectronics/stm32cubeh5/blob/main/Projects/STM32H573I-DK/Applications/OpenBootloader/README.md#_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: C
CODE:
```
OPENBL_CommandsTypeDef USART_Cmd =
{
  NULL,
  NULL,
  NULL,
  OPENBL_USART_ReadMemory,
  OPENBL_USART_WriteMemory,
  NULL,
  NULL,
  NULL,
  NULL,
  NULL,
  NULL,
  NULL,
  NULL,
  NULL,
  NULL,
  NULL,
  NULL,
  NULL,
  NULL,
  NULL
};

USART_Handle.p_Ops = &USART_Ops;
USART_Handle.p_Cmd = &USART_Cmd;           /* Initialize the USART handle with the list of supported commands */
OPENBL_USART_SetCommandsList(&USART_Cmd);  /* Register the list of supported commands in MW side */
```

