TITLE: ThreadX Memory Allocation - STM32CubeIDE
DESCRIPTION: This snippet demonstrates how to add a memory section for ThreadX in the STM32CubeIDE linker script (.ld). It defines a ._threadx_heap section within the RAM_D1 region, allocating 64KB of memory for ThreadX.
SOURCE: https://github.com/stmicroelectronics/stm32cubeh5/blob/main/Projects/NUCLEO-H503RB/Applications/USBX/Ux_Device_CDC_ACM/README.md#_snippet_2

LANGUAGE: LD
CODE:
```
._threadx_heap :
  {
     . = ALIGN(8);
     __RAM_segment_used_end__ = .;
     . = . + 64K;
     . = ALIGN(8);
   } >RAM_D1 AT> RAM_D1
```

