TITLE: Generating self-signed device certificate
DESCRIPTION: This snippet generates a self-signed device certificate using OpenSSL.  It creates an elliptic curve private key, generates a certificate signing request, and creates a self-signed certificate. These certificates are for testing and should NOT be used in production environments due to their short expiration and lack of proper security practices.
SOURCE: https://github.com/stmicroelectronics/stm32cubeh5/blob/main/Middlewares/ST/netxduo/addons/azure_iot/azure-sdk-for-c/sdk/samples/iot/docs/how_to_iot_hub_samples_linux.md#_snippet_5

LANGUAGE: bash
CODE:
```
~$ cd azure-sdk-for-c/sdk/samples/iot/

~/azure-sdk-for-c/sdk/samples/iot$ openssl ecparam -out device_ec_key.pem -name prime256v1 -genkey
~/azure-sdk-for-c/sdk/samples/iot$ openssl req -new -days 1 -nodes -x509 -key device_ec_key.pem -out device_ec_cert.pem -extensions client_auth -config x509_config.cfg -subj "/CN=paho-sample-device1"
~/azure-sdk-for-c/sdk/samples/iot$ openssl x509 -noout -text -in device_ec_cert.pem
```

