DESCRIPTION: This code snippet demonstrates how to add a new section named `._threadx_heap` to the STM32CubeIDE linker script (.ld) file. This section defines a 64KB heap for ThreadX dynamic memory allocation, ensuring it's properly aligned and located between the `.bss` and `._user_heap_stack` sections within the `RAM_D1` memory region.
SOURCE: https://github.com/stmicroelectronics/stm32cubeh5/blob/main/Projects/STM32H573I-DK/Applications/USBX/Ux_Device_CDC_ECM/README.md#_snippet_2

LANGUAGE: Other
CODE:
```
._threadx_heap :
  {
     . = ALIGN(8);
     __RAM_segment_used_end__ = .; 
     . = . + 64K;
     . = ALIGN(8);
   } >RAM_D1 AT> RAM_D1
```

