TITLE: Initializing Ethernet MAC Address in C
DESCRIPTION: This code snippet initializes the MAC address for the Ethernet interface. It sets the individual bytes of the MAC address within the `heth.Init.MACAddr` array. This is a crucial step for proper network communication.
SOURCE: https://github.com/stmicroelectronics/stm32cubeh5/blob/main/Projects/STM32H573I-DK/Applications/NetXDuo/Nx_TCP_Echo_Client/README.md#_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: C
CODE:
```
void MX_ETH_Init(void)
{

  /* USER CODE BEGIN ETH_Init 0 */

  /* USER CODE END ETH_Init 0 */

  /* USER CODE BEGIN ETH_Init 1 */

  /* USER CODE END ETH_Init 1 */
  heth.Instance = ETH;
  heth.Init.MACAddr[0] =   0x00;
  heth.Init.MACAddr[1] =   0x80;
  heth.Init.MACAddr[2] =   0xE1;
  heth.Init.MACAddr[3] =   0x00;
  heth.Init.MACAddr[4] =   0x00;
  heth.Init.MACAddr[5] =   0x00;
```

