TITLE: MDK-ARM Linker Configuration
DESCRIPTION: This snippet illustrates the configuration needed in MDK-ARM's linker file (.sct) or `tx_initialize_low_level.S` to define or modify the memory region used by ThreadX for dynamic memory allocation. Specifically, it shows how to define the `RW_IRAM1` region or modify the initialization line in `tx_initialize_low_level.S` to match the memory region being used.
SOURCE: https://github.com/stmicroelectronics/stm32cubeh5/blob/main/Projects/STM32H573I-DK/Applications/USBX/Ux_Device_CDC_ECM/README.md#_snippet_1

LANGUAGE: Assembly
CODE:
```
either define the RW_IRAM1 region in the ".sct" file
or modify the line below in "tx_initialize_low_level.S to match the memory region being used
    LDR r1, =|Image$$RW_IRAM1$$ZI$$Limit|
```

