TITLE: Simulated Interrupt Thread Template
DESCRIPTION: This is a template for a simulated interrupt thread that will occur periodically. It uses nanosleep to introduce a delay, then calls _tx_thread_context_save before calling the interrupt service routine (_sample_linux_interrupt_isr), and finally calls _tx_thread_context_restore.
SOURCE: https://github.com/stmicroelectronics/stm32cubeh5/blob/main/Middlewares/ST/threadx/ports/linux/gnu/readme_threadx.txt#_snippet_5

LANGUAGE: C
CODE:
```
void    *_sample_linux_interrupt_entry(void *p)
{
struct timespec ts;

    while(1)
    {

        ts.tv_sec = 0;
        ts.tv_nsec = 10000;
        while(nanosleep(&ts, &ts));

        /* Call ThreadX context save for interrupt preparation.  */
        _tx_thread_context_save();

        /* Call the real ISR routine */
        _sample_linux_interrupt_isr();

        /* Call ThreadX context restore for interrupt completion.  */
        _tx_thread_context_restore();
    } 
}
```

