TITLE: Assembly ISR Example for ThreadX on Cortex-M23
DESCRIPTION: This assembly code provides a template for creating an Interrupt Service Routine (ISR) in assembly language for ThreadX on Cortex-M23 using the GNU toolchain. It demonstrates how to push registers onto the stack, perform interrupt handling work, and pop the registers before returning from the interrupt. The `.thumb_func` directive ensures that the linker creates a thumb label, required for Cortex-M23 exception handlers.
SOURCE: https://github.com/stmicroelectronics/stm32cubeh5/blob/main/Middlewares/ST/threadx/ports/cortex_m23/gnu/readme_threadx.txt#_snippet_1

LANGUAGE: assembly
CODE:
```
    .global  your_assembly_isr
    .thumb_func
your_assembly_isr:
; VOID your_assembly_isr(VOID)
; {
        PUSH    {r0, lr}
;       
;    /* Do interrupt handler work here */
;    /* BL <your interrupt routine in C> */

        POP     {r0, r1}
        MOV     lr, r1
        BX      lr
; }
```

