TITLE: ThreadX Managed Interrupt Handler Template in Assembly
DESCRIPTION: This assembly code provides a template for a ThreadX managed interrupt service routine (ISR). It demonstrates the necessary steps for preserving the context and calling a C-based interrupt handler. The label `__tx_IntHandler` should be inserted into the interrupt vector table. Ensure the .thumb_func directive is used to instruct the linker to create thumb labels.
SOURCE: https://github.com/stmicroelectronics/stm32cubeh5/blob/main/Middlewares/ST/threadx/ports/cortex_m3/ac6/readme_threadx.txt#_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: Assembly
CODE:
```
        .global  __tx_IntHandler
        .thumb_func
__tx_IntHandler:
; VOID InterruptHandler (VOID)
; {
        PUSH    {r0, lr}

;    /* Do interrupt handler work here */
;    /* BL <your interrupt routine in C> */

        POP     {r0, lr}
        BX      lr
; }
```

