TITLE: Creating a Simulated Interrupt Thread
DESCRIPTION: This code snippet demonstrates how to create a simulated interrupt thread in Linux using pthreads. It creates the thread, and sets its priority using pthread_setschedparam with a SCHED_FIFO scheduling policy.
SOURCE: https://github.com/stmicroelectronics/stm32cubeh5/blob/main/Middlewares/ST/threadx/ports/linux/gnu/readme_threadx.txt#_snippet_4

LANGUAGE: C
CODE:
```
struct sched_param sp;

       /* Create the ISR thread */
       pthread_create(&_sample_linux_interrupt_thread, NULL, _sample_linux_interrupt_entry, &_sample_linux_interrupt_thread);

       /* Set up the ISR priority */
       sp.sched_priority = TX_LINUX_PRIORITY_ISR;
       pthread_setschedparam(_sample_linux_interrupt_thread, SCHED_FIFO, &sp);
```

