TITLE: Creating TAHI Library CMake
DESCRIPTION: This code snippet conditionally creates an imported shared library named `tahi`. The location of the library is set based on the `ENABLE_64` environment variable. Finally, it links the `test_utility` library with the `tahi` library if it exists.
SOURCE: https://github.com/stmicroelectronics/stm32cubeh5/blob/main/Middlewares/ST/netxduo/test/cmake/netxduo/regression/CMakeLists.txt#_snippet_38

LANGUAGE: cmake
CODE:
```
if("-DNX_TAHI_ENABLE" IN_LIST ${CMAKE_BUILD_TYPE})
  add_library(tahi SHARED IMPORTED)
  if($ENV{ENABLE_64})
    set_target_properties(tahi PROPERTIES IMPORTED_LOCATION
                                          ${SOURCE_DIR}/tahi_test/tahi64.so)
  else()
    set_target_properties(tahi PROPERTIES IMPORTED_LOCATION
                                          ${SOURCE_DIR}/tahi_test/tahi.so)
  endif()
  target_link_libraries(test_utility PUBLIC tahi)
endif()
```

