TITLE: ThreadX Interrupt Handler Template (Assembly)
DESCRIPTION: This assembly code provides a template for a ThreadX managed interrupt handler (ISR). It includes the necessary PUSH and POP instructions to preserve the context and allows access to ThreadX services from within the ISR. The label `__tx_IntHandler` must be placed in the interrupt vector table.
SOURCE: https://github.com/stmicroelectronics/stm32cubeh5/blob/main/Middlewares/ST/threadx/ports/cortex_m3/gnu/readme_threadx.txt#_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: assembly
CODE:
```
 .global  __tx_IntHandler
 .thumb_func
__tx_IntHandler:
; VOID InterruptHandler (VOID)
; {
 PUSH    {r0, lr}

; /* Do interrupt handler work here */
; /* BL <your interrupt routine in C> */

 POP     {r0, lr}
 BX      lr
; }
```

