TITLE: STM32CubeIDE Linker Configuration for ThreadX Memory Allocation
DESCRIPTION: This code snippet shows how to configure the STM32CubeIDE linker file to allocate a heap for ThreadX. A new section `._threadx_heap` is defined in the linker script within the `RAM_D1` region, with a size of 64KB. The section must be located between `.bss` and `._user_heap_stack`.
SOURCE: https://github.com/stmicroelectronics/stm32cubeh5/blob/main/Projects/STM32H573I-DK/Applications/USBPD/USBPD_SRC/README.md#_snippet_2

LANGUAGE: linker
CODE:
```
._threadx_heap :
  {
     . = ALIGN(8);
     __RAM_segment_used_end__ = .;
     . = . + 64K;
     . = ALIGN(8);
   } >RAM_D1 AT> RAM_D1
```

