TITLE: Standard IRQ Handler in ThreadX Assembly
DESCRIPTION: This assembly code defines the default IRQ handler (__tx_irq_handler) in tx_initialize_low_level.s for ThreadX. It saves the system context and then restores it after the application ISR call(s). This handler manages standard ARM IRQ interrupts by jumping to context save and restore routines.
SOURCE: https://github.com/stmicroelectronics/stm32cubeh5/blob/main/Middlewares/ST/threadx/ports_smp/cortex_a7_smp/ac5/readme_threadx.txt#_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: assembly
CODE:
```
    EXPORT  __tx_irq_handler
    EXPORT  __tx_irq_processing_return      
__tx_irq_handler
;
;    /* Jump to context save to save system context.  */
    B       _tx_thread_context_save             ; Jump to the context save
__tx_irq_processing_return
;
;    /* At this point execution is still in the IRQ mode. The CPSR, point of
;       interrupt, and all C scratch registers are available for use. Note 
;       that IRQ interrupts are still disabled upon return from the context
;       save function.  */
;
;    /* Application ISR call(s) go here!  */
;
;    /* Jump to context restore to restore system context.  */
    B       _tx_thread_context_restore
```

