TITLE: Building ThreadX Library Conditionally
DESCRIPTION: This snippet conditionally builds the ThreadX library using a shell script. If the build type is not "standalone_build", it executes the `run.sh` script to build the libraries, adds a custom target for building libraries, adds a dependency on this target for the netxduo target and sets include directories and imports the threadx library.
SOURCE: https://github.com/stmicroelectronics/stm32cubeh5/blob/main/Middlewares/ST/netxduo/test/cmake/crypto/CMakeLists.txt#_snippet_6

LANGUAGE: CMake
CODE:
```
if(NOT ("${CMAKE_BUILD_TYPE}" STREQUAL "standalone_build"))
  execute_process(COMMAND ${CMAKE_CURRENT_SOURCE_DIR}/run.sh build_libs)
  add_custom_target(build_libs ALL COMMAND ${CMAKE_CURRENT_SOURCE_DIR}/run.sh
                                           build_libs)
  add_dependencies(netxduo build_libs)
  target_include_directories(netxduo PUBLIC ${CMAKE_BINARY_DIR}/../libs/inc)
  add_library(threadx SHARED IMPORTED GLOBAL)
  add_library("azrtos::threadx" ALIAS threadx)
  set_target_properties(
    threadx PROPERTIES IMPORTED_LOCATION
                       ${CMAKE_BINARY_DIR}/../libs/threadx/libthreadx.so)
endif()
```

