TITLE: STM32CubeIDE ThreadX Heap Section
DESCRIPTION: This code snippet defines a `._threadx_heap` section in the STM32CubeIDE linker file (`.ld`). This section allocates 64KB of memory for the ThreadX heap, located between the `.bss` and `._user_heap_stack` sections. `__RAM_segment_used_end__` symbol is used to mark the end of used RAM.
SOURCE: https://github.com/stmicroelectronics/stm32cubeh5/blob/main/Projects/NUCLEO-H563ZI/Applications/NetXDuo/Nx_Iperf/README.md#_snippet_3

LANGUAGE: linker
CODE:
```
._threadx_heap :
{
   . = ALIGN(8);
   __RAM_segment_used_end__ = .;
   . = . + 64K;
   . = ALIGN(8);
} >RAM AT> RAM
```

