TITLE: Shared Data TLV Header Structure in C
DESCRIPTION: Defines the structure of the TLV header used at the beginning of the shared data area. It contains a magic number (`tlv_magic`) for identification and the total length (`tlv_tot_len`) of the shared TLV area, including the header itself. All fields are little-endian.
SOURCE: https://github.com/stmicroelectronics/stm32cubeh5/blob/main/Middlewares/Third_Party/mcuboot/docs/design.md#_snippet_17

LANGUAGE: C
CODE:
```
/** Shared data TLV header.  All fields in little endian. */
struct shared_data_tlv_header {
    uint16_t tlv_magic;
    uint16_t tlv_tot_len; /* size of whole TLV area (including this header) */
};
```

