TITLE: Copying Configuration Files with CMake
DESCRIPTION: This snippet demonstrates how to use CMake to copy configuration files from one directory to another. It first creates a directory and then uses `configure_file` with the `COPYONLY` option to duplicate the files.
SOURCE: https://github.com/stmicroelectronics/stm32cubeh5/blob/main/Middlewares/ST/usbx/test/cmake/usbx/CMakeLists.txt#_snippet_1

LANGUAGE: CMake
CODE:
```
# Use customized ux_user.h
set(UX_USER_FILE ${CMAKE_CURRENT_SOURCE_DIR}/ux_user.h)

# Copy files instead of using symlink
# libs/ -> ../libs/
file(MAKE_DIRECTORY ${CMAKE_CURRENT_SOURCE_DIR}/libs)
configure_file(${CMAKE_CURRENT_SOURCE_DIR}/../libs/CMakeLists.txt
               ${CMAKE_CURRENT_SOURCE_DIR}/libs/CMakeLists.txt COPYONLY)
configure_file(${CMAKE_CURRENT_SOURCE_DIR}/../libs/nx_user.h
               ${CMAKE_CURRENT_SOURCE_DIR}/libs/nx_user.h COPYONLY)
```

