TITLE: Default IRQ Handler in Assembly
DESCRIPTION: This assembly code defines the default IRQ handler (__tx_irq_handler) and the return point (__tx_irq_processing_return) for standard ARM IRQ interrupts in tx_initialize_low_level.s. It saves the system context by jumping to _tx_thread_context_save, provides a space for application-specific ISR calls, and restores the system context by jumping to _tx_thread_context_restore. The handler assumes that IRQ interrupts are disabled upon return from the context save function.
SOURCE: https://github.com/stmicroelectronics/stm32cubeh5/blob/main/Middlewares/ST/threadx/ports/cortex_a7/ac5/readme_threadx.txt#_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: assembly
CODE:
```
EXPORT  __tx_irq_handler
EXPORT  __tx_irq_processing_return      
__tx_irq_handler
;
;    /* Jump to context save to save system context.  */
    B       _tx_thread_context_save             ; Jump to the context save
__tx_irq_processing_return
;
;    /* At this point execution is still in the IRQ mode. The CPSR, point of
;       interrupt, and all C scratch registers are available for use. Note 
;       that IRQ interrupts are still disabled upon return from the context
;       save function.  */
;
;    /* Application ISR call(s) go here!  */
;
;    /* Jump to context restore to restore system context.  */
    B       _tx_thread_context_restore
```

