TITLE: Managed Interrupt Handler in Assembly for Cortex-M0 ThreadX
DESCRIPTION: This code snippet shows an example of an Interrupt Service Routine (ISR) written in assembly language for Cortex-M0 targets using ThreadX. The ISR pushes and pops registers r0 and lr for context preservation before performing ISR-specific operations.  'your_assembly_isr' is an entry point defined for the vector table.
