TITLE: Simulated Interrupt Thread Template in C
DESCRIPTION: Provides a template for a simulated interrupt thread that executes periodically. It includes sleeping for a desired time, saving and restoring the ThreadX context, and calling the application's ISR (Interrupt Service Routine).
SOURCE: https://github.com/stmicroelectronics/stm32cubeh5/blob/main/Middlewares/ST/threadx/ports/win32/vs_2019/readme_threadx.txt#_snippet_3

LANGUAGE: C
CODE:
```
DWORD WINAPI _sample_win32_interrupt(LPVOID *ptr)
{


    while(1)
    {

        /* Sleep for the desired time.  */
        Sleep(18);

        /* Call ThreadX context save for interrupt preparation.  */
        _tx_thread_context_save();

        /* Call application ISR here!  */

        /* Call ThreadX context restore for interrupt completion.  */
        _tx_thread_context_restore();
    }
}
```

