TITLE: Moving Context Objects in Memory
DESCRIPTION: This code demonstrates how a context object should be able to be moved in memory. This ensures that applications that populate a context on the stack of an inner function and then copy the context upwards through the call chain, or applications written in a language with automatic memory management that can move objects on the heap will still work.
SOURCE: https://github.com/stmicroelectronics/stm32cubeh5/blob/main/Middlewares/Third_Party/mbed-crypto/docs/architecture/alternative-implementations.md#_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: c
CODE:
```
mbedtls_xxx_context ctx1, ctx2;
mbedtls_xxx_init(&ctx1);
mbedtls_xxx_setup(&ctx1, );
ctx2 = ctx1;
memset(&ctx1, 0, sizeof(ctx1));
mbedtls_xxx_do_stuff(&ctx2, );
mbedtls_xxx_free(&ctx2);
```

